channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

Civil liberty, whistleblower protection groups urge Congress to allow vote on Espionage Act reform amendment
item.description: Nearly 20 civil liberty groups are urging the House Rules Committee to allow a Floor vote on an amendment to reform the Espionage Act to protect journalists and whistleblowers.

item.title: AOC: Antisemitism Undermines Progressive Movement
item.description: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez of New York, a member of "the Squad" of extreme left-leaning House Democrats, said Monday that antisemitism is undermining the "progressive community."

item.title: CHAOS: Pro-Hamas Group Orders 'Day Of Rage' on NYC - Violence Erupts, Authorities Nowhere to Be Found
New docs show Bragg spent $1M on attorneys to address House probe of Trump case amid city budget cuts
item.description: Documents obtained by a good-government watchdog found New York DA Alvin Bragg had expended $1 million to an outside law firm in order to blunt congressional oversight of NY v. Trump.

item.title: Dr. Drew to Newsmax: Biden Shows Signs of Parkinson's
item.description: Famed television personality Dr. Drew Pinsky told Newsmax on Monday that President Joe Biden shows signs of the neurodegenerative disease Parkinson's.

item.title: Happening Now: Protests Rage at UCLA As Pro-Hamas Mob Bloodies Security Guard, Drags Around Fake Corpses
BlackRock adds new proxy advisory firm amid ESG criticism as critics say 'too little, too late'
item.description: As BlackRock was primed to announce a new proxy advisor partnership under its voting choice program, critics said it was "too little, too late."

item.title: LA Times/NORC Poll: Pols Use Trans Issues to Divert Attention
item.description: A recent poll reveals that a significant majority of Americans believe politicians use transgender issues to divert attention from crucial political issues, Breitbart reported.

item.title: Hilarious and Scary Scenes Unfold As Biden 'Attends' White House 'Juneteenth' Event
US v Hunter Biden trial enters day 7 with continued jury deliberations: 'Choices have consequences'
item.description: First son Hunter Biden's criminal trial in Delaware ended day 6 with jury deliberations, which will continue this week until a verdict in the case is reached.

item.title: Will Scharf to Newsmax: Hunter Trial Timing Calculated for November Election
item.description: Hunter Biden's trial is likely being timed so that, should he be convicted, sentencing would take place after the November election, where his father could pardon him without political consequences, Attorney Will Scharf told Newsmax on Monday.

item.title: Liquor Licenses at Trump Golf Courses in New Jersey Could Be Taken Away After Manhattan Fraud Conviction
Crucial primary races to be decided Tuesday, setting up fight for balance of power
item.description: Voters in Nevada, North Dakota, South Carolina and Maine head to the polls on Tuesday June 11 to cast ballots in crucial House and Senate primary elections

item.title: Israeli Special Forces Disguised as Palestinian Refugees for Hostage Rescue
item.description: Israeli special forces were disguised as Palestinians looking for a place to live when they rescued hostages from Gaza during the weekend, two Israeli security sources told ABC News.
